---
/**
 * Who we help — homepage section.
 *
 * Three-card grid linking to the three persona pillar pages. Sits between
 * Features and Standards in the homepage flow:
 *
 *   Hero → Problem → HowItWorks → Features → WhoWeHelp → Standards → Pricing → FAQ
 *
 * After the reader has seen what the product does and how it works, this
 * section answers "but is it for me specifically?" by naming the three
 * buyer segments and giving each a direct route into their own persona
 * page.
 *
 * Not a full persona page — just a homepage signpost. The real content
 * lives on /for/independent-inspectors, /for/inspection-companies, and
 * /for/local-authorities.
 */
---
<section class="border-t border-brand-100 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-700">
        Who we help
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
        Built for everyone who signs an inspection report.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
        From a single RPII-certified inspector to a council parks team
        managing hundreds of sites — InspectVoice is positioned for the
        realities of each.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="mx-auto mt-16 grid max-w-5xl gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <li>
        <a
          href="/for/independent-inspectors"
          class="group flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 transition hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-sm"
        >
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-brand-700">
            Independent inspectors
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-700">
            For self-employed RPII Annual Inspectors
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            Voice-dictated findings on-site, PDF reports generated before
            you leave, offline-first so signal is never an issue. Get your
            evenings back.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-brand-700">
            See how it fits
            <svg class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a
          href="/for/inspection-companies"
          class="group flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 transition hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-sm"
        >
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-brand-700">
            Inspection companies
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-700">
            For firms with multiple inspectors
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            One team, one standard, one audit trail. Consistent reports
            across every inspector, central oversight, offline-first sync.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-brand-700">
            See how it fits
            <svg class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a
          href="/for/local-authorities"
          class="group flex h-full flex-col rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 transition hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-sm"
        >
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-brand-700">
            Local authorities
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-700">
            For councils managing multi-site portfolios
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            Portfolio-scale oversight, defect tracking across inspection
            cycles, mixed in-house and contracted inspector workflows, UK
            data residency.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-brand-700">
            See how it fits
            <svg class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
